item.title: How do you
item.dc:creator: @kloplop321 kloplop321
item.description:
@kloplop321 wrote:

well for one, dont use the vb webbrowser to load shockwave flash into it(it may load but it is totaly glitchy) so use a flash shockwave object instead(go and right click on the toolbox top and click add items(goto COM) find shockwave flash object(there are 2) choose both and try both on there then change the URL but anyway(its not buggy) also the only defect of this is the auto-play thing which is stuck on the first frame, the SWF object will change its settings like playing to false when the last frame is hit or the actionscript has stop(); so you would need to make an On_form1_load type of thing where it would automaticly set it to play like AxShockwaveFlashObject1.playing() = true statement(im not in VB 2005 currently so i wouldn’t know perfectly) secondly you can also embed this into your application but not suggested as RuneHQ keeps up with the updates.

Also make sure your ULR or URL or what-ever is correct. Anyway–I would sugest the Shockwave flash object =) just requires a DLL to go with the porgram in the installation or application directory.

If you knew how to embedd a dll or have it in the application(which checks if it exists, then if false creates that DLL with the binary data from the resources. Anyway good day!
